text:
relaxng (XML validator) has an <https://relaxng.org/compact-tutorial-20030326.html#id2815185|interleave> operator for this sort of thing. Its been a while since I last wrote a gramamr but I think it would look something like this:
```grammar {
  start = element house { room*}
  room = element room { box &amp; ((red &amp; blue?) | (blue &amp; red?)) }
  box = elem box { "box" }
  red = elem ball { "red"}
  blue = elem ball { "blue" }
}```

elements.text:
grammar {
  start = element house { room*}
  room = element room { box & ((red & blue?) | (blue & red?)) }
  box = elem box { "box" }
  red = elem ball { "red"}
  blue = elem ball { "blue" }
}
